<TITLE> HRC boss wins bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 29 (bdnews24.com) -- HRC Group's founding chairman and CEO Sayeed Hossain Chowdhury and GATCO directors Syed Galib Ahmed and Syed Tanvir Ahmed won bail from the High Court in separate cases Tuesday. Justice Sharifuddin Chaklader and Justice Mohammad Imdadul Haque Azad passed the bail orders after they filed appeals. In another development, Uttara Group owner Giridhari Lal Modi also won bail from the High Court. Partex Group chairman and former lawmaker MA Hashem received bail from the same court in a separate case. The HC also granted bail to Jamaat-e-Islami leaders Dr Abdullah Mohammad Taher and Gazi Nazrul Islam. bd
